{{Quote|When the Jedi anthropologists were ready to depart, they had asked the elders of ghôsh Windu if they might take with them a child to train in the Jedi arts, thus recovering the Force talents of the Korunnai to serve the peace of the galaxy. That would be me.|Mace Windu (allegedly), ''[[The Private Journals of Mace Windu]]''|<ref name="Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref>}}
'''Ghôsh Windu''' was the [[Korun/Legends|Korunnai]] tribe/family to which [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]] belonged. It was once loosely affiliated with [[Ghôsh Rostu]].

Windu and his "brother" [[Kar Vastor]] were the only known remaining members of the [[ghôsh]] by 22 BBY. All other members were [[Death/Legends|killed]] in the [[Summertime War]]. The ghôsh nearly died out after Windu was killed at the hands of [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]], however, Kar Vastor lived on.

